<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 31 at 11:15AM CDT  by NWS Kansas City</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of eastern Lafayette
County through 1145 AM CDT...
At 1114 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Oak Grove, moving northeast at 60 mph.
HAZARD...Nickel size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Higginsville, Waverly, Corder, Alma, Blackburn, Mayview, Dover and
Aullville.
This includes Interstate 70 in Missouri between mile markers 42 and
57.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
